10/05/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- US Ambassador to Belgrade Michael Polt does not believe that Serbia-Montenegro's former poor image will re-emerge. 
During comments at the 5th Summit on Serbia-Montenegro, which began Monday (9 May), Polt stressed that the federal union needs to maintain momentum for reforms. 
He also reaffirmed US support for economic development and improved living standards in the country.
In other news, Belgrade begins hosting a two-day EBRD workshop on fighting money laundering and terrorist financing Wednesday. 
The seminar, directed at Serbian banks, is the first of its kind to be held in Serbia-Montenegro. 
(Danas - 10/05/05; Beta, FoNet, EBRD Web site - 09/05/05)
